<br>
Mass group buff still wins out as most useless.<br>
<br>
Someone suggested having the pet do a lot more then explode.   If the haste was closer to 250% and the attack was up about 200 points with at least 100 AC and sure even toss in some HP.   Then the skill would be worthwhile.<br>
<br>
Think about it, a fully buffed epic hits for about the same as a paladin right now?   Putting it to 250% haste would end up making it almost monk level for a whopping 30 seconds, then of course it explodes.   And you can't use FB again for a long while.<br>
<br>
Thats the only case it would be moderately useful.. And even then, consider that dire charmed pets are about 3 times that level.  (Yeah, almost a monk x 3, scary ain't it?) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udalmathius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalmathius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 10:29:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: FB is bad, how to fix though?</span><hr size=1> As someone who does do high end Luclin encounters regularly you can take that negative side effects to the skill ideas you have and toss them out the window. In Luclin the likes of Arch Lich, High Priest, Burrower and especially mobs like the Curse from the basement cycle (40+ minute battle btw) take such a tremendous amount of mana that 3 Mages with Shields of Auras are hard pressed to keep up.  All I was able to do was Shield/Mod  and click Harnessed flame dirk on MT's. Doing ANYTHING else and we would lose so to even consider a skill that might contribute even a massive amount of increased damage at the cost of reducing our ability to supply the raid with much needed mana is pointless.<br>
<br>
Frenzied Burnout needs to be 144 min refresh or even longer, last 2-3 minutes in duration, get rid of the poofing or exploding crap entirely, give pets a 80-90% haste, 5-10% chance per round of Flurrying, and add +200-300 atk (any other statistical increase like str, dex, ac is really irrelevant when dealing with High end encounters the only thing that matters is your pets attack which like pcs determines how much of his MAX damage he does and how often he hits, this is why all higher end melees prefer VoG over SoS from enchanters epic, they are more than willing to give up the slight increase in haste to deal higher damage and hit more often)<br>
<br>
This would maybe increase your pets maximum damage output to *maybe* 50-75% or even possibly double (and ONLY during those 2-3 minutes time, would NOT make a huge difference but be hella nice for the end of a fight) and considering fact that mod rod 2.0 and the design of Luclin encounters has basically relegated us into the role as SOLE manadumpers for entire raids would kind of make up for our lack of beng able to contribute damage while we are busting our ass cranking out mana to insure our success.  And wouldnt be unbalancing in any way because of the fact that we really have no choice (unless you like losing to the big mobs) but to make mod rods for the raid and would give us a little dignity and feeling of adding somthing else besides manawhoring to a raid.<br>
<br>
Dalmathius Darkenfyre<br>
